<div id="review_199498254" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/199498254" />
    <a title="Mark Rice" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4787077-mark-rice"><img alt="Mark Rice" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442456917p2/4787077.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/199498254?book_show_action=true">Aug 17, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mark Rice" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mark Rice" href="/user/show/4787077-mark-rice">Mark Rice</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer199498254" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11798716115502846062">I&apos;m a huge fan of Irvine Welsh at his creative best. <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/23955.Trainspotting' title='Trainspotting by Irvine Welsh' rel='nofollow noopener'>Trainspotting</a>, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/527862.The_Acid_House' title='The Acid House by Irvine Welsh' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Acid House</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/23965.Porno' title='Porno by Irvine Welsh' rel='nofollow noopener'>Porno</a> are funny, clever and brimming with originality. <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/212534.The_Bedroom_Secrets_of_the_Master_Chefs' title='The Bedroom Secrets of the Master Chefs by Irvine Welsh' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Bedroom Secrets of the Master Chefs</a>, on the other hand, is an uninspired story devoid of Welsh&apos;s trademark witty dialogue.</span>
  <span id="freeText11798716115502846062" style="display:none">I'm a huge fan of Irvine Welsh at his creative best. <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/23955.Trainspotting" title="Trainspotting by Irvine Welsh" rel="nofollow noopener">Trainspotting</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/527862.The_Acid_House" title="The Acid House by Irvine Welsh" rel="nofollow noopener">The Acid House</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/23965.Porno" title="Porno by Irvine Welsh" rel="nofollow noopener">Porno</a> are funny, clever and brimming with originality. <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/212534.The_Bedroom_Secrets_of_the_Master_Chefs" title="The Bedroom Secrets of the Master Chefs by Irvine Welsh" rel="nofollow noopener">The Bedroom Secrets of the Master Chefs</a>, on the other hand, is an uninspired story devoid of Welsh's trademark witty dialogue.</span>
